  "texts": [
    "This suggests that both RL PPO ED and RL A2C ED outperform GA across various contexts, emphasizing their effectiveness in addressing the evaluated tasks.Upon examination, it is evident that the average WCETs identified by the RL algorithms, A2C and PPO, are significantly higher than those identified by the GA approach.",
    "This distinction underscores the RL algorithms' effectiveness in exploring and understanding the execution space of the target application, thereby pinpointing scenarios that lead to the WCET more reliably.",
    "Comparatively, the GA approach falls short of reaching the WCET estimates achieved by the RL algorithms.",
    "One reason for the better performance of RL over GA could be the continuous exploration inherent in the RL experiment.",
    "Specifically, when RL is running a trajectory, it can apply a torque to a joint motor."
